OL,3,CThe homeless people hoping for change
OL,4,Cafter election day
OL,6,FRichard, aged 50, has been sleeping
OL,7,Frough in Exeter for the past few
OL,8,Fweeks. He didn't want us to show his
OL,9,Fface.J"The main thing is sleep
OL,10,Fdeprivation," he said.
OL,12,F"You're worried about whether you're
OL,13,Fgoing to be attacked, you're worried
OL,14,Fabout whether you're going to get
OL,15,Frained on, too cold, and generally
OL,16,Fthere just isn't anywhere for anyone
OL,17,Fto really sleep and be out of the
OL,18,Fwind, out of the rain."
